<br>
All I'm saying is this. your character's journey through the game is that character's life.  Things happen that your character can't control, or didn't plan for.  This, to me, is some of the beauty of roleplaying, the not always knowing how any given conversation, or encounter may turn out. Obviously, this is not always....erm, feasible.  But when something unexpected happens, something you didn't plan for,roll with it, as your character would, which means, of course, getting to know your character at least a little. <br>
And remember, this is supposed to be fun.*Smile*<br>
