<br>
Unexpected encounters in the game can do more for your character development than all the pre-conceived ideas you had about your character to begin with.  Your current storyline, Sarhea, reminds me somewhat of some storylines I had going on on my old server.  Reminds me a lot, actually.  Just as in RL things happen to us that we couldn't have imagined, that change us sometimes, the same happens in the game.  You (not you Sarhea, but &quot;you&quot; in general) might think your character is a pure evil type who can never feel pity or love or any &quot;light&quot; emotions, or a pure goody two-shoes who would never under any circumstances have anything to do with a dark elf, and then you meet someone or you find yourself in a situation where you feel your character changing from what you thought they were.  And that's when RP is best, when you're that in tune with your character that you feel them changing in a way you couldn't have predicted.<br>
<br>
